Chinese Recipe: 星洲炒米粉, Final Recipe: Title: Hainanese Chicken Rice, Ingredients: 1. 1 (3 pound) whole chicken. 2. salt to taste. 3. water to cover. 4. 1 onion, halved (skin on). 5. 8 cloves garlic, peeled. 6. 1 (1 inch) piece fresh ginger, sliced. 7. salt and ground white pepper to taste. 8. Rice:. 9. 3 cups long-grain white rice. 10. 5 cloves garlic, sliced. 11. 1 (1/2 inch) piece fresh ginger, sliced. 12. 2 teaspoons oil. 13. 5 pandan leaves, knotted. 14. Dipping Sauces:. 15. 3 fresh red chile peppers, halved and seeded. 16. 1 lime, juiced, or as needed. 17. 4 cloves garlic, peeled. 18. 1 slice fresh ginger. 19. Garnish:. 20. 10 leaves lettuce, or as desired. 21. 1 cucumber, peeled and sliced. 22. 1 tomato, sliced. 23. 1 tablespoon light soy sauce. 24. 1 teaspoon sesame oil. , Steps: 1. Remove fat from the chicken and reserve it for later use. Season chicken, inside and out, with salt.. 2. Bring a large pot of water to a boil; add chicken, onion, 8 garlic cloves, sliced 1-inch piece ginger, salt, and white pepper. Bring liquid back to a boil, reduce heat, and simmer until chicken is fully cooked, 20 to 25 minutes. An instant-read thermometer inserted into the thickest part of the thigh, near the bone should read 165 degrees F (74 degrees C).. 3. Carefully remove chicken and plunge into a large bowl of ice water until cooled. Remove chicken, dry, and cut chicken into bite-size pieces. Strain chicken broth and reserve liquid.. 4. Wash and drain rice.. 5. Heat reserved chicken fat in a skillet over medium heat; cook and stir 5 sliced garlic cloves and sliced 1/2-inch piece ginger until fragrant, about 1 minute. Add rice and oil; cook and stir until rice is coated in oil. Pour in enough reserved chicken broth to cook rice, about 6 cups. Add pandan leaves. Cover skillet and cook rice until tender and broth is absorbed, 20 to 30 minutes.. 6. Pound red chile peppers using a mortar and pestle, adding a small amount of salt, until peppers transform into a fine paste. Stir enough lime juice into paste to make smooth; transfer to a serving dish.. 7. Pound 4 garlic cloves and 1 slice ginger using a mortar and pestle until paste is formed; transfer to a separate serving dish.. 8. Place lettuce leaves on a serving plate and arrange cucumber slices and tomatoes around dish. Place the chicken pieces in the center. Mix soy sauce and sesame oil together in a bowl; pour over chicken. Serve a bowl of reserved chicken broth on the side with a bowl of rice and the 2 dipping sauces..
Chinese Recipe: 扬州炒饭, Final Recipe: Title: Yangzhou Fried Rice, Ingredients: 1. 1 cup long-grain white rice, rinsed several times in cold water until water runs clear. 2. 3 tablespoons vegetable or peanut oil. 3. 8 scallions (white and green parts), thinly sliced on diagonal (about 1 cup). 4. 4 ounces fresh shrimp, peeled, deveined, and finely diced (about 1 cup or 6 large shrimp). 5. 3 large eggs, lightly beaten. 6. 4 ounces fresh shiitake mushroom, stems discarded and caps finely diced (about 2 cups). 7. 4 ounces fresh or frozen peas (about 1 cup). 8. 4 ounces ham, finely diced (about 1 cup). 9. 1 tablespoon oyster sauce. 10. 1 teaspoon sugar. 11. 1 teaspoon kosher salt. 12. 1/2 teaspoon ground white pepper. , Steps: 1. In medium saucepan over high heat, combine rice and 1 1/4 cups water. Cover and bring to boil, then reduce heat to low and simmer until water is absorbed, about 25 minutes. Remove from heat and let stand, covered, 10 minutes. Fluff with large fork or chopsticks, then cool. (Rice can be made ahead and refrigerated, covered, up to 2 days.). 2. In wok or heavy large saute pan over moderately high heat, heat oil until hot but not smoking. Add half of scallions (reserve remainder for garnish). Add shrimp and stir-fry until shrimp are pink and cooked through, 2 to 3 minutes. Add eggs and rice and stir-fry until eggs are just set, about 1 minute. Add mushrooms, peas, ham, oyster sauce, sugar, salt, and pepper and stir-fry until heated through and fluffy, 4 to 5 minutes. Garnish with remaining scallions and serve..
Chinese Recipe: 鸡丝凉面, Final Recipe: Title: Cilantro Chicken And Spicy Thai Noodles, Ingredients: 1. For the chicken. 2. 4 chicken thighs, boneless and skinless (about 1 pound). 3. 3 tablespoons canola oil. 4. salt & freshly ground black pepper. 5. 2 tablespoons garlic, minced. 6. 1/4 cup cilantro leaf. 7. 2 limes, zest of 1 lime and juice of both. 8. 2 tablespoons seasoned rice vinegar. 9. For the sauce. 10. 2 tablespoons canola oil. 11. 1 tablespoon fresh ginger, peeled and grated. 12. 1 lime, zested and juiced. 13. 2 garlic cloves, minced. 14. 1/4 teaspoon red pepper flakes. 15. 1 cup chicken stock. 16. salt & freshly ground black pepper. 17. 1 tablespoon thai green curry paste. 18. 1 tablespoon seasoned rice vinegar. 19. 3 scallions, white and green parts-chopped. 20. 1 lb spaghetti, cooked al dente and sprayed with canola oil (keep warm). 21. 1 carrot, shredded. 22. 1/4 cup roasted peanuts, crushed. , Steps: 1. For the chicken, combine all the ingredients in a nonreactive bowl and let stand at room temperature for 20 minutes. Prepare a grill pan to medium-high heat and grill the chicken thighs 4 minutes per side or until done.. 2. For the sauce, add canola oil to a saute pan over medium heat. Add the ginger, lime zest, juice, garlic, red pepper flakes and chicken stock. Stir well to combine and sprinkle with salt and pepper. Add the curry paste, seasoned rice vinegar and scallions. Reduce the heat to low and simmer 2 minutes.. 3. Place the cooked noodles in a large serving bowl and add sauce, carrots and peanuts - toss well. Add the cilantro chicken and serve..
Chinese Recipe: 凉拌豆芽, Final Recipe: Title: Chinese Bean Sprout Salad, Ingredients: 1. 1 bag Bean sprouts. 2. 1 Cucumber. 3. 1 can Canned tuna. 4. 5 slice Ham. 5. 1 White sesame seeds (optional). 6. 2 tbsp Soy sauce. 7. 2 tbsp Sugar. 8. 2 tbsp Vinegar. 9. 2 tbsp Sesame oil. 10. 1 tsp Chinese soup stock. , Steps: 1. Parboil or briefly microwave the bean sprouts Cut the cucumber and ham into thin strips.. 2. Lightly drain the excess oil from the tuna.. 3. Transfer all the ingredients to a bowl.. 4. Combine the ingredients and make the dressing.. 5. Pour the Step 2 dressing over the Step 1 ingredients.. 6. Mix well, and let them absorb the flavour in the fridge for about 30 minutes (drain the excess water if you prefer).. 7. And it's done.. 8. "Cellophane Noodle Salad"It uses the same flavouring ingredients..
Chinese Recipe: 酸菜猪肉饺子, Final Recipe: Title: Pork Dumplings, Ingredients: 1. 8 ounces ground pork (or any other meat/fish filling). 2. 1 tablespoon minced ginger. 3. 1 tablespoon minced garlic. 4. 2 tablespoons finely chopped green onions. 5. 1 cup of finely chopped napa cabbage. 6. 1/4 cup water chestnut, chopped. 7. 2 tablespoons soy sauce. 8. 2 teaspoons cornstarch. 9. 1 tablespoon olive oil. 10. 1 package wonton wrappers or 1 package gyoza skins. 11. 1 egg white. 12. 3 tablespoons peanut oil. 13. Dipping Sauce. 14. 1 teaspoon sesame oil. 15. 3 tablespoons soy sauce. 16. 1 tablespoon toasted sesame seeds. , Steps: 1. Cook cabbage for 1-2 minutes in enough water to cover the bottom of the pan.. 2. Remove from heat and drain water.. 3. Saute pork in olive oil until cooked.. 4. Add ginger, garlic, sesame seeds, onions, chestnuts, cabbage, soy, corn starch and mix until blended and remove from heat.. 5. Brush wonton wrapper with egg white and add one spoonful of meat mixture.. 6. Fold bottom of wrapper over top and seal into a half crescent.. 7. Tighten seal with fingers.. 8. Shallow fry dumplings in peanut oil at medium heat flipping over once, until browned on one side.. 9. Serve with dipping sauce.. 10. To make dipping sauce: Mix together and serve with dumplings..
Chinese Recipe: 简单盐焗鸡, Final Recipe: Title: Salted Chicken, Ingredients: 1. 3 kg coarse rock salt. 2. 1/2 cup fennel seed, cracked. 3. 2 eggs, beaten. 4. 2 lemons, halved. 5. 1 tablespoon peppercorn. 6. 1 bunch fresh thyme. 7. olive oil. 8. 1 (2 kg) whole chickens. 9. 1 bunch parsley, chopped. 10. 8 garlic cloves, skins left on, squashed. , Steps: 1. Preheat the oven to 200 C or 400 degrees F.. 2. Put all the salt into a bowl with the fennel seeds, eggs, lemon juice (save the juiced lemon skins), peppercorns and a wineglass of water and mix together.. 3. Crush the thyme in a pestle and mortar and add a couple good glugs of olive oil.. 4. Rub this flavoured oil all over your chicken, pushing any extra inside the cavity along with the parsley, garlic and squeezed lemon halves.. 5. You want the cavity so full that no salt will be able to get in.. 6. Get four long pieces of tinfoil and put them on top of each other to make a sheet around a metre square.. 7. Lay on a third of the salt, spreading until it is about 1/4 inch thick.. 8. Put your chicken on top, then pack the rest of the salt around it, making sure not to pierce the skin.. 9. Carefully fold up the sides of the tinfoil and scrunch it at the top.. 10. You can rip off any extra tinfoil.. 11. Place the chicken in the preheated oven and cook for two hours.. 12. Remove and allow to rest for 15 minutes.. 13. Take it to the table, rip open the tinfoil and crack the salt crust.. 14. It will fall apart easily and you will have a juicy chicken ready to serve.. 15. A nice side dish is some horseradish, mixed with creme fraiche or some homemade mayonnaise and basil..
Chinese Recipe: 老虎菜, Final Recipe: Title: "The Dish", Ingredients: 1. 1 lb. ground meat. 2. 3 medium onions, chopped. 3. 3 medium bell peppers, chopped. 4. 2 c. white cream-style corn. 5. 1 1/2 c. tomato paste. 6. 1 c. ripe olives and juice. 7. 1/2 tsp. salt. 8. 1 Tbsp. sugar. 9. 1 to 2 Tbsp. chili powder. 10. 1 (8 oz.) pkg. noodles. 11. 1 lb. sharp cheese, grated. , Steps: 1. Saute meat in a small amount of vegetable oil.. 2. Add onions and pepper and cook until they are almost done.. 3. Add remaining ingredients, except noodles and cheese.. 4. Cook the mixture for 45 minutes..
Chinese Recipe: 椒盐虾, Final Recipe: Title: Salt and Pepper Shrimp, Ingredients: 1. 1 lb large shrimp in their shells (25). 2. 6 cups vegetable oil. 3. 3/4 teaspoon fine sea salt. 4. 1/2 teaspoon freshly ground black pepper. 5. 1/2 teaspoon Chinese five-spice powder. 6. Special equipment: a deep-fat thermometer. , Steps: 1. Cut each shrimp shell lengthwise along back with scissors, leaving last segment intact, then devein shrimp, leaving shell in place.. 2. Cut off feathery legs and sharp pointed section of shell above soft tail fins.. 3. Rinse shrimp and dry thoroughly.. 4. Heat oil in a wok or deep heavy pot over high heat until it registers 400F on deep-fat thermometer.. 5. Deep-fry shrimp in 4 batches until shells bubble and shrimp are bright pink, 45 to 60 seconds (they will be slightly undercooked), returning oil to 400F between batches.. 6. Transfer with a slotted spoon to paper towels to drain.. 7. Carefully pour oil into a heatproof bowl (to cool before discarding), then wipe wok clean with paper towels.. 8. Stir together salt, pepper, and five-spice powder.. 9. Heat wok or a heavy skillet over moderate heat until hot but not smoking, then add deep-fried shrimp and spice mix and stir-fry 10 seconds..
Chinese Recipe: 拍黄瓜, Final Recipe: Title: Calm Cucumbers, Ingredients: 1. 4 cucumbers, pared. 2. 1 sweet Spanish onion, sliced. 3. 1 c. sugar. 4. 1 c. water. 5. 1/2 c. vinegar. 6. 1/2 c. oil. 7. celery seed. , Steps: 1. Score cucumbers lengthwise with tines of fork.. 2. Slice thinly and put in salted ice water with onion.. 3. Let stand 1 to 2 hours. Cook sugar and water over low heat until sugar is dissolved. Cool.. 4. Add vinegar and oil and mix well.. 5. Drain cucumbers and onion.. 6. Pour vinegar and oil mixture over them.. 7. Cover and refrigerate overnight.. 8. Sprinkle with celery seed before serving. Good with beans.. 9. Yields 8 servings..
Chinese Recipe: 土豆炖牛肉, Final Recipe: Title: Beef Stew With Star Anise, Ingredients: 1. 1 liter vegetable stock or 1 liter chicken stock. 2. 450 g beef rump, washed and cut into slivers. 3. 3 garlic cloves, peeled and finely chopped. 4. 1 cinnamon stick. 5. 4 star anise. 6. 2 tablespoons light soy sauce. 7. 2 tablespoons Thai fish sauce. 8. 1 teaspoon granulated sugar. 9. 115 g bean sprouts, remove tail and head cap. 10. 1 scallion, finely chopped. 11. 1 bunch fresh coriander, coarsely chopped (cilantro). , Steps: 1. Pour the stock into a large, heavy pan. Add the beef, garlic, chopped coriander roots, cinnamon sticks, star anise, soy sauce, fish sauce and sugar. Bring to the boil, then reduce the heat to low and simmer for 30 minutes.. 2. Skim off any form that rises to the surface of the liquid with a slotted spoon.. 3. Meanwhile, divide the bean sprouts among four individual serving bowls. Remove and discard the cinnamon sticks and star anise from the stew with a slotted spoon.. 4. Ladle the stew over the bean sprouts, garnish with the chopped scallions and chopped fresh coriander (cilantro) and serve immediately..
Chinese Recipe: 红豆汤, Final Recipe: Title: Red Bean Soup, Ingredients: 1. 1/2 lb adzuki beans. 2. 1 lb pork, cut into chunks. 3. 1 large carrot. 4. 1 large onion. 5. 3 large celery ribs, with leaves. 6. 1 1/2 teaspoons basil. 7. 1 1/2 teaspoons marjoram. 8. 2 teaspoons black pepper. 9. 2 teaspoons salt. 10. 4 cups water. 11. 1/4 cup sherry wine (medium dry). , Steps: 1. Boil the Adzuki beans until they are slightly soft.. 2. Drain the water and rinse the beans, place them back in a large pot.. 3. Chop up the carrots, celery, and onions, and place them in the pot with the beans.. 4. Add the rest of the ingredients (spices, pork, water), except the sherry.. 5. Mix the ingredients.. 6. Cover and bring to a boil.. 7. Reduce heat and cook just under a boil for 2 to 3 hours (until beans are very soft, soup is thick and vegetables have thoroughly cooked).. 8. Before serving, add the sherry and stir.. 9. I like a particularly thick,"stew like" soup.. 10. If you want a thinner soup, just add more water!. 11. Also, I tend to add my spices liberally- just season to taste!. 12. The pork is mainly to give flavour, so get something with a little fat on it!. 13. Note: Adzuki beans are Japanese beans.. 14. You can substitute with other beans, but the cooking time may vary..
Chinese Recipe: 回锅肉, Final Recipe: Title: All in the Pot soup, Ingredients: 1. 1/2 onion. 2. 1/2 green pepper. 3. 1 clove garlic. 4. 1 bunch fresh kale. 5. 2 leeks. 6. 1 pinch basil. 7. 1 box beef stock. 8. 1 salt&pepper. 9. 6 small red potatoes. 10. 3 carrots. , Steps: 1. add first three ingredients to soup pot and saute. 2. once they start to brown and kale and leeks till kale wilts. 3. throw in basil and broth...u can use any broth u have this is a follow ur taste buds recipe. 4. have it simmer for 15min.. 5. while u wait cut potatoes into nice bite size pieces and carrots into rounds. 6. add to pot and simmer for another 25min.. 7. or untill potatoes and carrots are tender. 8. at the time of putting in your potatoes u can add cauliflower or green beans... Whatever suits ur taste buds!. 9. salt and pepper to taste and presto soups on..
Chinese Recipe: 鱼香茄子, Final Recipe: Title: Smoked Eggplant with Fragrant Spices, Ingredients: 1. 2 medium eggplant. 2. 1 tablespoon coriander seeds. 3. 2 teaspoons cumin seeds. 4. 1 teaspoon turmeric. 5. 1 x salt to taste. 6. 1 teaspoon cayenne pepper. 7. 1/2 cup peanut oil. 8. 1 large onions chopped. 9. 2 teaspoons garlic minced. 10. 1-2 each serrano chiles minced. 11. 2 each tomatoes chopped. 12. 1 teaspoon garam masala. 13. 1 teaspoon lemon juice. 14. 1 cup cilantro coarsely chopped. , Steps: 1. Place the eggplants directly over the gas burner, or grill over a wood fire.. 2. Cook on all sides until the skin is black and charred and the flesh feels soft when pierced with a fork.. 3. Grind the coriander and cumin seeds, and mix with the turmeric, salt and red pepper on a small plate.. 4. Set near the stove.. 5. Peel the eggplants, being sure to remove all the black, charred skin, and wipe them clean with wet hands.. 6. Squeeze out all the water.. 7. Chop the eggplants coarsely and set aside.. 8. Heat the oil in a heavy, shallow pan.. 9. Add onion and cook, stirring frequently, until it turns almost reddish brown, 10 or 12 minutes.. 10. Stir in the garlic and cook until the mixture turns reddish brown, stirring and scraping the bottom of the pan.. 11. Stir in the spices and green chiles and cook, stirring for about l0 seconds.. 12. Add the tomatoes and let the mixture simmer until the tomatoes form a sauce and oil separates from the sauce.. 13. Stir in the eggplant and cook for 10 to 15 minutes, until the oil again separates from the sauce.. 14. Taste for salt, stir in the garam masala, lemon juice and cilantro.. 15. Serve hot or cold with Indian bread as a side dish..
Chinese Recipe: 酱油炒饭, Final Recipe: Title: Fried Rice With Sweet Soy Sauce, Ingredients: 1. FRIED RICE. 2. 3 tablespoons peanut oil, divided. 3. 4 large eggs, lightly beaten. 4. 3 finely chopped shallots. 5. 2 garlic cloves, minced. 6. 1 serrano chili, chopped. 7. 4 cups cooked long-grain brown rice. 8. 2 tablespoons sweet soy sauce (recipe is below). 9. 1/4 teaspoon salt. 10. 1/4 teaspoon black pepper. 11. 1 1/2 cups thinly sliced daikon radishes. 12. 1/3 cup fresh basil leaf. 13. 1/3 cup mint leaf. 14. 1/3 cup fresh cilantro. 15. 4 lime wedges. 16. FOR SOY SAUCE. 17. 1/4 cup low sodium soy sauce. 18. 1/4 cup packed dark brown sugar. , Steps: 1. Heat 1 tablespoon oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat, swirl to coat.. 2. Pour eggs into pan, and cook for 2 minutes, or until set, stirring once.. 3. Remove eggs from pan.. 4. Increase heat to high, and add remaining 2 tablespoons oil to pan.. 5. Add shallots, garlic, and chile, stir-fry for 1 minute.. 6. Add rice, and stir-fry for 3 minutes, or until lightly browned.. 7. Add cooked eggs, soy sauce, salt, and pepper, toss to combine.. 8. Top with radish, and herbs, and serve with lime.. 9. FOR THE SWEET SOY SAUCE:. 10. Combine soysauce and brown sugar in a sauce pan, and bring to a boil over medium heat.. 11. Simmer 2 minutes or until rediced to 1/4 cup..
Chinese Recipe: 手擀面, Final Recipe: Title: Handkerchiefs with Spinach, Garlic and Pecorino Cheese, Ingredients: 1. 1 recipe Basic Fresh Egg Pasta dough. 2. 2 tbsp. salt. 3. 4 fl. oz. extra-virgin olive oil. 4. 8 cloves garlic, thinly sliced. 5. 1 cup dry white wine. 6. 2 lb. fresh spinach leaves, cleaned, stemmed, torn into pieces approximately 3 inches square. 7. 1 cup grated pecorino cheese (preferably from Siena). , Steps: 1. Bring 6 quarts water to a boil and add 2 tbsp.. 2. salt.. 3. Roll the Basic Fresh Egg Pasta dough out into 4 sheets, using the thinnest setting.. 4. Cut each sheet of pasta using a jagged pastry cutter into 4-inch squares.. 5. Set aside, and cover.. 6. Heat the olive oil in a large 12- to 14-inch skillet.. 7. Saute the garlic over medium heat until light brown.. 8. Add white wine and bring to a boil, turn the heat off and set aside.. 9. Drop the pasta into the boiling water and cook 1 to 2 minutes until tender yet al dente.. 10. Drain the pasta in a colander over sink and pour into saute pan.. 11. Turn heat to high, add spinach and toss until spinach is wilted but not completely shapeless.. 12. Stir in pecorino cheese and pour into warm serving bowl.. 13. Serve immediately..
Chinese Recipe: 小米粥, Final Recipe: Title: Congee with Vegetables and Fresh Herbs, Ingredients: 1. 1 cup long-grain brown rice, soaked in 3 cups of water overnight. 2. 1 sweet potato, peeled and diced. 3. 2 stalks lemongrass, bruised (see page 155). 4. 7 cups vegetable or chicken stock or water. 5. Salt. 6. 2 teaspoons minced fresh ginger. 7. 2 tablespoons olive oil. 8. 1 bunch bok choy, trimmed and finely diced. 9. 2 scallions, green and white parts, thinly sliced. 10. 1 large handful fresh cilantro leaves. 11. 1/2 cup coarsely chopped toasted peanuts or almonds. 12. Soy sauce for serving. 13. Sesame oil for serving. 14. Red pepper flakes for serving. , Steps: 1. Drain the rice and place it in a large pot with the sweet potato.. 2. Cut the lemongrass stalks in half horizontally and add them to the pot.. 3. Add the stock and 1 tablespoon salt and bring to a boil.. 4. Decrease the heat and simmer, covered, for 35 minutes.. 5. Remove the lid and increase the heat so the rice is bubbling.. 6. Remove the lemongrass and discard.. 7. Simmer, stirring frequently to prevent it from sticking, until the rice is tender and has the consistency of a thick porridge, about 15 minutes more.. 8. Add the ginger in the last 5 minutes of cooking.. 9. Heat a saute pan over medium-high heat and add the olive oil.. 10. Add the bok choy and cook until tender and wilted, about 4 minutes.. 11. Season with salt and remove from the heat.. 12. To serve, put the bok choy, scallions, cilantro, and nuts into small bowls.. 13. Ladle the porridge into bowls and let diners garnish it with the vegetables, nuts, soy sauce, sesame oil, and red pepper flakes.. 14. We know that brown rice has more nutrients than white rice, but aside from health concerns, white rice is put through many stages of processing, all requiring fossil fuels and chemicals.. 15. First, the germ and bran are removed to extend the length of time the rice can be stored; then synthetic vitamins are added back in; and finally, the rice is polished with water, glucose, or the mineral talc, which is known to cause stomach cancer.. 16. The taste of brown rice can take some getting used to, but cooked with fragrant seasonings like the ones in the congee recipe, it can please even the pickiest of palates..
Chinese Recipe: 脆皮日本豆腐, Final Recipe: Title: Indian Tofu, Ingredients: 1. Olive oil spray. 2. 1 cup basmati rice. 3. 6 to 8 ounces extra-firm tofu, drained and pressed. 4. 1/2 cup dry red wine. 5. 1 serrano chile, stemmed, seeded, and chopped. 6. 1/2 teaspoon garam masala. 7. 1/2 teaspoon ground turmeric. 8. 1/4 teaspoon ground cumin. 9. 1/8 teaspoon sea salt. 10. 1/4 medium onion, chopped. 11. One 15-ounce can lentils, drained and rinsed. 12. 1 large Anaheim green chile, roasted, stemmed, seeded, peeled, and chopped (see headnote). 13. 2 cups bite-size cauliflower florets. 14. 1/2 medium zucchini, quartered lengthwise and thickly sliced (about 2 cups). 15. 2 or 3 medium tomatoes, diced, or one 14-ounce can, drained and chopped. , Steps: 1. Preheat the oven to 450F.. 2. Spray the inside and lid of a cast-iron Dutch oven with olive oil.. 3. Rinse the rice in a strainer under cold water until the water runs clear.. 4. Pour the rice into the pot.. 5. Add 1 cup plus 1 tablespoon water (or vegetable broth) and stir to coat the grains and spread them in an even layer.. 6. Squeeze the tofu as dry as possible and cut into 1-inch cubes.. 7. Place in a medium bowl.. 8. In a measuring cup, mix the wine with the serrano chile, garam masala, turmeric, cumin, and salt.. 9. Drizzle over the tofu while stirring the cubes.. 10. Scatter the onion in the pot.. 11. Add the lentils and spread in an even layer.. 12. Blanket with the roasted chile.. 13. Arrange the tofu in a layer in the pot.. 14. Top with layers of the cauliflower, zucchini, and tomatoes.. 15. Cover and bake for about 30 minutes, or until 3 minutes after the aroma of a fully cooked meal escapes the oven.. 16. Serve immediately.. 17. Calories: 610. 18. Protein: 25g. 19. Carbohydrates: 107g. 20. Fat: 4g. 21. Cholesterol: 0. 22. Sodium: 968mg. 23. Fiber: 12g.
Chinese Recipe: 蜜汁排骨, Final Recipe: Title: Baby Back Pork Ribs Glazed with Honey, Ingredients: 1. 4 racks baby back pork ribs, about 2 3/4 lbs each (see Notes). 2. 1/4 cup prepared yellow mustard. 3. 1/4 cup water. 4. 1 tablespoon Worcestershire sauce. 5. 1 tablespoon apple cider vinegar. 6. 6 tablespoons mild chili powder, preferably Chimayo, Ancho or Hatch. 7. 3 tablespoons sweet paprika. 8. 3 tablespoons firmly packed dark brown sugar. 9. 1 1/2 teaspoons dry mustard. 10. 2 1/4 teaspoons coarsely ground fresh black pepper. 11. 3/4 teaspoon Old Bay Seasoning. 12. 1 teaspoon ground cinnamon (optional). 13. 1 cup firmly packed light brown sugar. 14. 1 cup honey. 15. 1/4 cup apple juice. 16. 1 cup Apple Barbecue Sauce or your favorite BBQ sauce. 17. 1/2 cup honey. 18. 2 tablespoons apple cider vinegar. 19. 1/2 Granny Smith apple, peeled cored and grated on a Microplane grater. 20. About 1/2 cup Apple Juice Spray. 21. 1 cup unsweetened apple juice. 22. 1 cup water. 23. 1/2 cup canola or vegetable oil. 24. 5 garlic cloves, peeled and coarsely chopped. 25. 1 medium sweet white onion coarsely chopped. 26. 1 green bell pepper coarsely chopped. 27. 2 teaspoons kosher salt, plus additional as needed. 28. 1/4 cup bourbon. 29. 3 tablespoons chile powder. 30. 1 tablespoon coarsely ground fresh black pepper. 31. 1/4 teaspoon ground allspice, plus additional for seasoning. 32. 1/4 teaspoon ground cloves, plus additional for seasoning. 33. 1 cup firmly packed dark brown sugar. 34. 2 cups water. 35. 2 cups ketchup. 36. 1/2 cup unsulfured blackstrap molasses. 37. 1/2 cup prepared yellow mustard. 38. 1/2 cup apple cider vinegar, plus additional as needed. 39. 2 teaspoons hot sauce. 40. 1/2 cup apricot preserves. 41. 1 jalapeno chili, grated on a Microplane grater, stopping before the seeds. 42. 1/2 Granny Smith apple, grated on a Microplane grater. , Steps: 1. Preheat an indirect barbecue drip pan and fruitwood (preferably apple), a ceramic cooker with deflector plate and fruitwood (preferably apple) or a charcoal or gas grill with a box or packet of fruitwood (preferably apple) to 275 degrees Fahrenheit.. 2. Combine all of the Mustard Moisturizer ingredients.. 3. Combine all of the seasoning blend ingredients.. 4. Rub a thin layer of the Mustard Moisturizer on all sides of the racks and lightly sprinkle with the seasoning blend on all sides.. 5. The remaining seasoning blend will be used later in the cooking.. 6. If using a ceramic cooker, the racks can be placed an inch apart on a rib.. 7. They might need to be trimmed to fit the cooking surface so the lid can close.. 8. If using a larger indirect or direct barbecue, no additional trimming is necessary.. 9. Place the ribs in the cooker and cook for 2 hours.. 10. Meanwhile, combine the Wrapping Mixture ingredients.. 11. Tear off 8 sheets of heavy-duty aluminum foil.. 12. Working with 2 sheets of foil at a time, place a quarter of the Wrapping Mixture on the foil, top with a rack of ribs, and wrap in the foil, crimping to seal.. 13. Wrap with the second sheet of foil.. 14. Repeat for three remaining 3 racks of ribs.. 15. If using a ceramic cooker, stack the packets on top of each other.. 16. If using a smoker, place the ribs on sheet pans for easier movement.. 17. Place the packets back in the cooker, meat side down, and cook for 1 hour, flipping half way through.. 18. Remove the racks from the cooker and let rest in the foil packets for 20 minutes.. 19. Remove the ribs from the foil and dust lightly on both sides with additional seasoning blend.. 20. Place the ribs back in the cooker, meat side up, for 30 minutes.. 21. Meanwhile, combine the Honey BBQ Sauce ingredients.. 22. Remove the racks from the cooker and brush with an even, but not too thick layer of sauce.. 23. The layer should evenly coat the ribs but should not clump.. 24. Place meat in the cooker, meat side up, for 25 minutes to tighten up the sauce.. 25. Paint a cutting board with some of the remaining sauce.. 26. Remove the ribs from the cooker and place on the prepared cutting board adding additional sauce as needed to cover, but not excessively coat.. 27. Spray twice with apple juice spray.. 28. Cut the ribs from the racks and dredge to coat the exposed sides with the remaining BBQ sauce.. 29. For APL BBQ Sauce:. 30. Pour the oil in a large saucepan and cook over medium heat until it starts to shimmer.. 31. Stir in garlic, onion, bell pepper and salt.. 32. Cook, stirring occasionally until the vegetables have softened, about 10 minutes.. 33. Pour in the bourbon and cook until the alcohol has cooked off, about 5 minutes.. 34. There will no longer be the strong smell of alcohol.. 35. Combine the chili powder, black pepper, allspice and cloves and add to the pan.. 36. Cook, stirring continuously, until fragrant, about 3 minutes.. 37. Stir in the brown sugar, water, ketchup, molasses, mustard, vinegar, hot sauce and preserves.. 38. Bring the mixture to a boil, stirring occasionally to be sure nothing sticks to the bottom and burns.. 39. Reduce to a simmer.. 40. Continue to simmer, stirring often, until thickened, about 45 minutes.. 41. Add the jalapeno and apple.. 42. At this point the sauce can be left chunky or blended in a blender (blend in small batches since it will be hot), or in a bowl using an immersion/stick blender until smooth.. 43. Season to taste with additional allspice, cloves, salt and vinegar to taste.. 44. For Apple Juice Spray: Combine the water and juice and place in a spray bottle.. 45. (For Apricot Spray, substitute apricot nectar for apple juice.).
Chinese Recipe: 春卷, Final Recipe: Title: Shanghai Pork And Shrimp Spring Rolls, Ingredients: 1. 1/2 teaspoon sugar. 2. 1/2 teaspoon cornstarch. 3. 1/2 lb pork tenderloin or 1/2 lb pork sirloin roast, cut into 2 inch long matchsticks. 4. 1/3 lb medium shrimp, peeled, deveined and coarsely chopped. 5. 3 dried shiitake mushrooms (large). 6. 1 1/2 tablespoons cornstarch. 7. 3 tablespoons vegetable oil. 8. 1 teaspoon grated ginger. 9. 2 garlic cloves, minced. 10. 1/2 cup shredded bamboo shoot. 11. 1/2 lb bean sprouts. 12. salt, to your taste. 13. pepper, to your taste. 14. 18 spring rolls, skins. 15. oil (for deep frying). 16. 1 tablespoon cornstarch. 17. 1/2 cup water. , Steps: 1. Combine sugar, 1/2 teaspoon cornstarch, soy sauce, pork, and shrimp in a bowl and stir. Set aside.. 2. In a bowl, rehydrate shitake mushrooms in hot water just enough to cover until softened. Depending on mushrooms used this can take anywhere between 15-30 minutes to soften. Reserve the liquid for dissolving cornstarch. Cut off the stem and cut into very thin match stick pieces.. 3. In a small cup dissolve 1 1/2 T cornstarch with 3 T of reserved mushroom soaking liquid. This will be used to thicken the filling mixture.. 4. Heat 1 1/2 T oil in a large skillet over medium high heat and add ginger and garlic. Cook for about 30 seconds until fragrant but not browned and add pork and shrimp mixture. Stir constantly to separate the pork pieces and shrimp into nuggets and cook for about 2 minutes. Do not overcook. Transfer to a dish.. 5. Add the remaining 1 1/2 T oil to the skillet on medium high heat. Add shitake mushrooms, bamboo shoots, bean sprouts, salt and pepper. Cook 5 minutes stirring constantly. Return the pork and shrimp mixture to the skillet and stir to combine. Lower the heat and give the cornstarch mixture a stir and pour over the filling. Cook for about 30 seconds to bind the mixture. Transfer to a bowl to cool completely.. 6. In a small cup combine 1 T cornstarch with 1/2 C water to seal spring roll skin.. 7. Lay a spring roll skin on the work surface making sure one of the pointy corner is facing you. Put about 2 T of filling slightly below the center towards you and form into log shape using your fingers.. 8. Lift the bottom edge towards you up and over the filling tucking the point under it. Fold in the sides and brush the upper edges with cornstarch and water mixture. Roll away from you (bottom up) to seal. Set the finished rolls seam side down on the baking sheet covered with wax paper or aluminum foil and keep covered with a kitchen towel to prevent drying.. 9. Heat 1 inch of oil in a deep skillet over medium high to about 350F degrees. Slide in a few spring rolls and fry, turning as needed for about 3 minutes or until golden brown and very crisp.. 10. Remove from the oil and drain. Continue with the remaining rolls. To serve, cut diagonally in half. Serve with a vinegar or dipping sauce of your choice..
Chinese Recipe: 湖南小炒肉, Final Recipe: Title: Hunan Pork Stir-Fry, Ingredients: 1. 1/2 lb. boneless lean pork. 2. 2 tsp. cornstarch. 3. 6 Tbsp. lite soy sauce, divided. 4. 2 cloves garlic, minced and divided. 5. 3/4 c. water. 6. 1 Tbsp. cornstarch. 7. 1/8 to 1/4 tsp. crushed red pepper. 8. 3 Tbsp. vegetable oil, divided. 9. 3 c. bite sized cauliflowerets. 10. 1 medium size green pepper, chunked. 11. 2 medium tomatoes, cut in eighths. 12. hot, cooked rice. , Steps: 1. Cut pork across the grain into thin slices, then into strips. Combine 2 tablespoons each cornstarch and lite soy sauce with 1/2 of the garlic in small bowl; stir in pork.. 2. Let stand 30 minutes..
Chinese Recipe: 鸡汤面, Final Recipe: Title: Chicken Noodles, Ingredients: 1. 4 12 lbs skinless chicken thighs. 2. 6 chicken bouillon cubes. 3. 1 lb egg noodles. 4. 1 lb carrot. 5. 1 teaspoon thyme. 6. 1 tablespoon salt. 7. 1 tablespoon coarse black pepper. 8. 12 cups water. 9. 12 cup reduced-fat milk. , Steps: 1. Boil chicken in a dutch oven until fully cooked.. 2. discard the water, fat, skin and bones.. 3. Set chicken aside on a plate.. 4. Pour 12 cups of fresh water the bouillon cubes,thyme and bring to a boil and make sure bouillon cubes have dissolved.. 5. add sliced carrots (I like the peeled ones in the bag).. 6. Reduce heat add the chicken that was set aside and the egg noodles let simmer about 20 minutes, stirring and mixing occasionally.. 7. Then add salt and pepper to taste pour in the 1/2 cup of reduced fat milk.. 8. mix well, let cool about 10 minutes and serve..
Chinese Recipe: 西红柿鸡蛋面, Final Recipe: Title: Spaghetti With Bacon And Eggs, Ingredients: 1. 3/4 pound spaghetti. 2. 8 slices bacon. 3. 4 large eggs. 4. 1/2 cup plus 2 tablespoons grated Parmesan (about 3 ounces). 5. Kosher salt and pepper. , Steps: 1. Cook the pasta according to the package directions. Reserve 1/2 cup of the cooking water. Drain the pasta and return it to the pot.. 2. Meanwhile, cook the bacon in a non-stick or cast-iron skillet over medium heat until crisp, 6 to 8 minutes. Let cool, then break into pieces.. 3. Wipe out the skillet and return it to medium heat. Crack the eggs into the skillet; cook until the whites are set but the yolks are still runny, 3 to 4 minutes.. 4. Toss the pasta with the bacon, 1/2 cup of the Parmesan, 1/2 teaspoon salt, 1/4 teaspoon pepper, and the reserved pasta water.. 5. Divide the pasta among bowls and top with the eggs. Sprinkle with the remaining 2 tablespoons of Parmesan..
Chinese Recipe: 番茄蛋汤, Final Recipe: Title: Tomato Egg Soup, Ingredients: 1. 2 qt. chicken broth. 2. 2 c. stewed tomatoes, mashed into small pieces. 3. 2 Tbsp. cornstarch, blended with 1/4 cup cold water. 4. 3 eggs, beaten. 5. 4 tender scallions, chopped (use all parts). , Steps: 1. In large. 2. pot, bring broth to boil.. 3. Add tomatoes. When mixture boils again, stir in cornstarch.. 4. Reduce heat and stir until soup thickens. Slowly stir beaten egg in simmering soup. When all the eggs have been stirred in, remove soup from heat. Serve. 5. immediately,. 6. sprinkled. 7. with. 8. raw,. 9. chopped scallions. Serves 6..
Chinese Recipe: 酸汤水饺, Final Recipe: Title: Asian Dumplings, Ingredients: 1. 1 pound ground pork. 2. 1/2 cup fresh ginger minced. 3. 2 heads napa cabbage shredded and chopped. 4. 5 cloves garlic fresh, minced. 5. 1 cup wild mushrooms chopped finely. 6. 1 tablespoon corn starch plus extra for plating. 7. 1 tablespoon sugar. 8. 1 1/2 tablespoons salt. 9. 1 cup warm water in shallow bowl. 10. 2 packages wonton wrappers. 11. 2 quarts water salted, for boiling. 12. 1/2 cup scallions chopped, optional. , Steps: 1. In a large bowl, combine first 8 ingredients (pork through salt, and scallions, if desired). Mix well.. 2. On a plate, place one wonton wrapper and wet the edges with warm water.. 3. Place one spoonful of the pork mixture in the center of the wonton.. 4. Fold wonton wrapper in half, over the mixture (use more warm water if nec.). 5. Pick up the dumpling and using water, pinch the ends together (make a seal). 6. Place on a plate that has been dusted with cornstarch.. 7. Repeat until mixture is completely distributed.. 8. Dust cornstarch on each layer of dumplings so they don't stick together.. 9. To cook: Bring the salted water to boil in a large pot.. 10. Place dumplings in boiling water, being careful not to overcrowd.. 11. Boil for 2-3 minutes. The dumpling centers will turn slightly opaque.. 12. Remove dumplings with slotted spoon.. 13. Serve immediately with soy sauce or see recommended sauce..
Chinese Recipe: 香辣牛肉面, Final Recipe: Title: Spicy Vietnamese Beef and Noodle Soup, Ingredients: 1. 5 tablespoons peanut oil. 2. 3 1/4 pounds meaty oxtails, patted dry. 3. 2 large onions, chopped. 4. 1 large carrot, peeled, chopped. 5. 3 stalks lemongrass,* chopped. 6. 2/3 cup chopped peeled fresh ginger. 7. 8 garlic cloves, chopped. 8. 7 whole star anise (star-shaped spice)*. 9. 1 tablespoon black peppercorns. 10. 12 cups water. 11. 7 cups canned beef broth (about four 14 1/2-ounce cans). 12. 3 tablespoons fish sauce (nam pla)*. 13. 1 12-ounce package fresh udon noodles (refrigerated Japanese wheat noodles)* or fresh linguine. 14. 1 tablespoon oriental sesame oil. 15. 3 cups bean sprouts. 16. 6 radishes, thinly sliced. 17. 4 green onions, thinly sliced. 18. 4 serrano chilies, thinly sliced. 19. 6 tablespoons chopped fresh basil. 20. 6 tablespoons chopped fresh mint. 21. 6 tablespoons chopped cilantro. 22. Lime wedges. 23. Additional fish sauce (nam pla). , Steps: 1. Heat peanut oil in heavy large pot over medium-high heat.. 2. Sprinkle oxtails with salt and pepper.. 3. Add oxtails to pot and brown on all sides, about 20 minutes.. 4. Transfer oxtails to large bowl.. 5. Add onions and next 6 ingredients to same pot.. 6. Saute until vegetables are tender, about 8 minutes.. 7. Return oxtails to pot.. 8. Add 12 cups water, beef broth and 3 tablespoons fish sauce.. 9. Cover and simmer gently until oxtails are very tender, about 3 hours.. 10. Using tongs, transfer oxtails to large bowl.. 11. Strain broth into another large pot; discard solids.. 12. Remove meat from oxtails; discard bones.. 13. Add meat to broth.. 14. Refrigerate overnight.. 15. Spoon solid fat off top of soup.. 16. Cook noodles in large pot of boiling salted water until tender.. 17. Drain; rinse under cold water.. 18. Return to same pot.. 19. Toss noodles with sesame oil.. 20. Bring soup to boil.. 21. Divide noodles, sprouts and next 6 ingredients among 6 bowls.. 22. Ladle soup into bowls.. 23. Serve with lime wedges and additional fish sauce.. 24. *Available at Asian markets and some supermarkets nationwide..
